413 static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
414 static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
415 
416 template <typename T>
417 class WeakCallbackInfo {
418  public:
419  typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
420 
421  WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
422  void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
423  Callback* callback)
424  : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
425  for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
426  embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
427  }
428  }
429 
430  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
431  V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
432  V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
433 
434  // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
435  // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
436  // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
437  // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
438  // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
439  // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
440  void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
441 
442  private:
443  Isolate* isolate_;
444  T* parameter_;
445  Callback* callback_;
446  void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
447 };
448 
449 
450 // kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
451 // will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
452 // will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
453 // actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
454 // possible to request a second pass callback.
455 enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };

646 template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
647  public:
651  V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
657  template <class S>
658  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
659  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
660  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
661  }
667  template <class S, class M2>
668  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
669  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
670  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
671  }
678  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {
679  Copy(that);
680  }
681  template <class S, class M2>
682  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
683  Copy(that);
684  }
685  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) {
686  Copy(that);
687  return *this;
688  }
689  template <class S, class M2>
690  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
691  Copy(that);
692  return *this;
693  }
699  V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
700  if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
701  }
702 
703  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
704  template <class S>
705  V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
706 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
707  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
708  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
709  if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
710 #endif
711  return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
712  }
713 
714  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
715  template <class S>
716  V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
717  return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
718  }
719 
720  private:
721  friend class Isolate;
722  friend class Utils;
723  template<class F> friend class Local;
724  template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
725  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
726 
727  explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
728  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
729  template<class S, class M2>
730  V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
731 };

7562 struct JitCodeEvent {
7563  enum EventType {
7564  CODE_ADDED,
7565  CODE_MOVED,
7566  CODE_REMOVED,
7567  CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
7568  CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
7569  CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
7570  };
7571  // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
7572  // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
7573  // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
7574  // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
7575  // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
7576  enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
7577 
7578  // There are two different kinds of JitCodeEvents, one for JIT code generated
7579  // by the optimizing compiler, and one for byte code generated for the
7580  // interpreter. For JIT_CODE events, the |code_start| member of the event
7581  // points to the beginning of jitted assembly code, while for BYTE_CODE
7582  // events, |code_start| points to the first bytecode of the interpreted
7583  // function.
7584  enum CodeType { BYTE_CODE, JIT_CODE };
7585 
7586  // Type of event.
7587  EventType type;
7588  CodeType code_type;
7589  // Start of the instructions.
7590  void* code_start;
7591  // Size of the instructions.
7592  size_t code_len;
7593  // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
7594  Local<UnboundScript> script;
7595  // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
7596  // code line information which is returned from the
7597  // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
7598  // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
7599  void* user_data;
7600

7651 enum RAILMode : unsigned {
7652  // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
7653  // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
7654  // Throughput may be throttled.
7655  PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
7656  // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
7657  // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
7658  // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
7659  PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
7660  // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
7661  // in this mode.
7662  PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
7663  // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
7664  // turn off latency optimizations.
7665  PERFORMANCE_LOAD
7666 };

9642 template <class T>
9643 class Maybe {
9644  public:
9645  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
9646  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
9647 
9651  V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
9652 
9657  V8_INLINE void Check() const {
9658  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
9659  }
9660 
9665  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
9666  if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
9667  return IsJust();
9668  }
9669 
9674  V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
9675  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
9676  return value_;
9677  }
9678 
9683  V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
9684  return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
9685  }
9686 
9687  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
9688  return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
9689  (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
9690  }
9691 
9692  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
9693  return !operator==(other);
9694  }
9695 
9696  private:
9697  Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
9698  explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
9699 
9700  bool has_value_;
9701  T value_;
9702 
9703  template <class U>
9704  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
9705  template <class U>
9706  friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
9707 };
9708 
9709 template <class T>
9710 inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
9711  return Maybe<T>();
9712 }
9713 
9714 template <class T>
9715 inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
9716  return Maybe<T>(t);
9717 }

9719 // A template specialization of Maybe<T> for the case of T = void.
9720 template <>
9721 class Maybe<void> {
9722  public:
9723  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !is_valid_; }
9724  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return is_valid_; }
9725 
9726  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
9727  return IsJust() == other.IsJust();
9728  }
9729 
9730  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
9731  return !operator==(other);
9732  }
9733 
9734  private:
9735  struct JustTag {};
9736 
9737  Maybe() : is_valid_(false) {}
9738  explicit Maybe(JustTag) : is_valid_(true) {}
9739 
9740  bool is_valid_;
9741 
9742  template <class U>
9743  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
9744  friend Maybe<void> JustVoid();
9745 };

11051 Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
11052 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11053  typedef internal::Address A;
11054  typedef internal::Internals I;
11055  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11056  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11057  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11058  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11059  if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11060  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11061  instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType) {
11062  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11063  A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(obj, offset);
11064 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
11065  // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
11066  // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
11067  value = I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(obj, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
11068 #endif
11069  internal::Isolate* isolate =
11070  internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(obj);
11071  A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
11072  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
11073  }
11074 #endif
11075  return SlowGetInternalField(index);
11076 }
11077 
11078 
11079 void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
11080 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11081  typedef internal::Address A;
11082  typedef internal::Internals I;
11083  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11084  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11085  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11086  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11087  if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11088  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11089  instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType)) {
11090  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11091  return I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, offset);
11092  }
11093 #endif
11094  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
11095 }

11657 int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
11658  int64_t change_in_bytes) {
11659  typedef internal::Internals I;
11660  constexpr int64_t kMemoryReducerActivationLimit = 32 * 1024 * 1024;
11661  int64_t* external_memory = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
11662  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);
11663  int64_t* external_memory_limit = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
11664  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryLimitOffset);
11665  int64_t* external_memory_at_last_mc =
11666  reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
11667  I::kExternalMemoryAtLastMarkCompactOffset);
11668 
11669  // Embedders are weird: we see both over- and underflows here. Perform the
11670  // addition with unsigned types to avoid undefined behavior.
11671  const int64_t amount =
11672  static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<uint64_t>(change_in_bytes) +
11673  static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory));
11674  *external_memory = amount;
11675 
11676  int64_t allocation_diff_since_last_mc =
11677  static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory) -
11678  static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory_at_last_mc));
11679  // Only check memory pressure and potentially trigger GC if the amount of
11680  // external memory increased.
11681  if (allocation_diff_since_last_mc > kMemoryReducerActivationLimit) {
11682  CheckMemoryPressure();
11683  }
11684 
11685  if (change_in_bytes < 0) {
11686  const int64_t lower_limit =
11687  static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory_limit) +
11688  static_cast<uint64_t>(change_in_bytes));
11689  if (lower_limit > I::kExternalAllocationSoftLimit) {
11690  *external_memory_limit = lower_limit;
11691  }
11692  } else if (change_in_bytes > 0 && amount > *external_memory_limit) {
11693  ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
11694  }
11695  return *external_memory;
11696 }

11698 Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
11699 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11700  typedef internal::Address A;
11701  typedef internal::Internals I;
11702  A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11703  A embedder_data =
11704  I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
11705  int value_offset =
11706  I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11707  A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(embedder_data, value_offset);
11708 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
11709  // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
11710  // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
11711  value =
11712  I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(embedder_data, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
11713 #endif
11714  internal::Isolate* isolate = internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(
11715  *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this));
11716  A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
11717  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
11718 #else
11719  return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
11720 #endif
11721 }

11730  I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
11731  int value_offset =
11732  I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11733  return I::ReadRawField<void*>(embedder_data, value_offset);
11734 #else
11735  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(index);
